<dl id="n35016i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35016i">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35016i"> 16(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> biddy pony</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">BIDET, commonly pronounced BIDDY. A kind of tub, contrived for ladies to wash themselves, for which purpose they bestride it like a little French poney, or post-horse, called in French bidets. <small> Captain Francis Grose, <a name="FGCD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FGCD"><cite title="source">A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue</cite></a> (1785) 00</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
